<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-1747] TestcaseEnv improperly shares state between instances</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-1747</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;TestcaseEnv in system tests uses class variables instead of instance variables for a bunch of state. This causes the data to persist between tests. In some cases this can cause tests to break (e.g. there will be state from a service running in a previous test that doesn&apos;t exist in the current test; trying to look up state about that service raises an exception or produces invalid data).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
